radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: CT scan of the head, face, and cervical spine
radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimally displaced fractures of the nasal bones bilaterally; no acute intracranial process or fractures of the cervical spine.
Restricted diffusion in the cortex of the right superior frontal gyrus; marked hyperintensity in the cortex and white matter of the adjacent right frontal lobe consistent with vasogenic edema.

Nonocclusive filling defect in the anterior aspect of the superior sagittal sinus, a filling defect in the cortical vein of the right frontal lobe, a punctate filling defect in the left internal jugular vein, and an area of mild hypodensity and swelling in the middle aspect of the right superior frontal gyrus.
